<font color="#FF0000">THIRTY YEARS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Apr 22 21:30:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This Memorial Day it will be 30 years to the day that I left Vietnam after two tours.  I plan to visit the Wall to pay my respects.  But for me it will also be a form of celebration.  A celebration of my life for those who gave theirs.  The &quot;why them and not me?&quot; issue has been settled and I can now be proud of what I am (a Vietnam Vet) and who I am.  I can now say that I did my job to the best of my ability for a 18 year old boy.  I can look at the Wall and still be moved to tears but this time it will be tears of joy.  This will be a time for me to say to them &quot;Look at me!&quot;.  I am here because of you.  You and this memorial have made me who I am today!  It was a long struggle but I am here!  It is a celebration of life as well as a offer of respect and thanks for those who did not return. <br>
So I will offer respect and honor.  I will raise a glass to my friends who couldn't be with me this day.  Those living as well as those who didn't return.  God Bless you!
<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


